Evaluating the constraint algebra under the canonical Poisson bracket relation confirms that closure is cleanly preserved at the level of the truncated quadratic EFT:
\(\{\mathcal{C}_{1},\mathcal{C}_{2}\}\equiv 0\)
This first-class structure is strictly preserved within the perturbative regime up to the absolute boundary of the designated EFT truncation order. Calculating the remaining phase-space parameters leaves exactly three physical scalar degrees of freedom representing the decoupled metric potentials and the gauge-invariant scalar lattice mode.



